_meta.description: Unified Malay/Manglish lexicon for normalization and dialect handling.

penang.pi mai pi mai tang tu: pergi balik pergi balik di situ juga

colloquialisms.mamak: Indian-Muslim restaurant or person. Popular 24-hour eateries in Malaysia.
colloquialisms.jalan-jalan: Walk around, stroll, go out for leisure.
colloquialisms.makan angin: Go on vacation, literally 'eat wind'. Taking a break.
colloquialisms.kopi-o: Black coffee without milk. 'O' from Hokkien for black.
colloquialisms.gila: Crazy, but often used as intensifier for 'very'.
colloquialisms.nasi lemak: Coconut rice with sambal, Malaysia's national dish.
colloquialisms.canoneer: Cannon minion in MOBA games (e.g., Mobile Legends / League of Legends).
colloquialisms.sahur: Makan sebelum subuh (biasanya pada bulan Ramadan).
colloquialisms.lepas sahur: Selepas makan sahur; awal pagi sebelum subuh.
